					<h3> The Meeting </h3>
					<p>
						On the second day of 2010, I met Rick Robinson.
						We had both answered the same BandMix ad.
						On what was possibly the coldest morning ever, some people who ostensibly wished to gather and play music,
						instead met for breakfast in a Burger King.
						Granted, not a bad plan by our host: see what manner of human shows up before allowing them in your house.
						In fact, we were a benign and awkward group.
						I do recall a guy in a fedora bailing, once he realized he was one of a group of four to five guitar players,
						in a Burger King, on possibly the coldest morning ever.
					</p>

					<p>
						After a little back-and-forth, a few of us did gain entry to that guy's basement, where we played some rather uninspired covers.
						Rick and I ended up off to the side, exchanging a couple things we'd written.
						Mine was a jazzy thing that would become <i>One More Fool</i>,
						and we did a little jam off of Rick's <i>Andeline</i> (which also ended up on the album).
						There wasn't much other vibe to be found, and I thought that was that.
					</p>
				</div>
