					<h3> The Process </h3>
					<p>
						I believe, after a couple months, Rick reached out to me.
						It may have been the other way 'round.
						I may have started the music for some of these by then.  Maybe not.
						Whatever the case, we ultimately produced these tracks between March and December of 2010, and never once recorded together.
					</p>
					<p>
						I wrote music, organized into what felt like coherent songs, recorded draft versions, and sent them off to Rick.
						He wrote lyrics, recorded layers and layers of vocal parts, and added some guitars and live percussion.
						He then sent them back for incorporation into the master copy in Tracktion.
						Eventually, I added guitars, keys, bass, and programmed the final Groove Agent drum tracks.
						And then, at last, produced final mixes, completed nearly a year to the day removed from that cold morning ...
					</p>
